[server.js](/C:/Users/ColsonR/curriculum_render/railway-server/server.js) now treats grading and appeals as thin proxy calls. `/api/ai/grade` and `/api/ai/appeal` forward the incoming body to `GRADING_PROXY_URL` with a 35s timeout, then fall back to the client’s keyword/current score if the proxy is unavailable. The extracted grading internals are out of this file now: no `GradingQueue`, no Groq grading calls, no JSON repair/parsing helpers, no MCQ cap logic, and no framework-built appeal prompt.

[grading-engine.js](/C:/Users/ColsonR/curriculum_render/js/grading/grading-engine.js) now sends `keywordScore` on grade requests and `currentScore` on appeal requests, and it blocks appeal downgrades on the client side as a guardrail. I also separated the redox chat path from the deleted grading queue; if that feature is used, configure `REDOX_CHAT_API_URL`, `REDOX_CHAT_API_KEY`, and optionally `REDOX_CHAT_MODEL`.

Config/docs were updated in [railway-server/.env.example](/C:/Users/ColsonR/curriculum_render/railway-server/.env.example), [railway-server/.env](/C:/Users/ColsonR/curriculum_render/railway-server/.env), [.gitignore](/C:/Users/ColsonR/curriculum_render/.gitignore), and [railway-server/README.md](/C:/Users/ColsonR/curriculum_render/railway-server/README.md). I also rewrote [tests/grading/escalation-e2e.test.js](/C:/Users/ColsonR/curriculum_render/tests/grading/escalation-e2e.test.js) to validate proxy forwarding and fallback behavior instead of the removed inline Groq implementation.

Verification: `node --check` passed for [server.js](/C:/Users/ColsonR/curriculum_render/railway-server/server.js), [grading-engine.js](/C:/Users/ColsonR/curriculum_render/js/grading/grading-engine.js), and [escalation-e2e.test.js](/C:/Users/ColsonR/curriculum_render/tests/grading/escalation-e2e.test.js). A direct Node harness against the extracted route code passed for grade fallback, appeal fallback, proxy forwarding, and appeal downgrade blocking. I could not run `npx vitest` or `npm test` here because there is no local `vitest` install in this workspace and the sandbox cannot fetch packages from npm.
